Output 3 — Global Defaults / Resolved Formatting Design
Goal:

Create a production-ready formatting model where:
1. Global defaults define the normal formatting behavior.
2. Sheet defaults optionally refine formatting by sheet type.
3. Column definitions only call out overrides when they differ from defaults.
4. Template creation applies broad defaults first, then sparse overrides.
5. Dashboard Quality Sections A–G validate the resolved formatting contract.
6. Section G validates date formats from resolved formatting, not legacy test assumptions.
This design is intended for the next script after v1.5.42, before modularization.

