  -> metadata-only refresh OR full template build
The all-template entrypoint is here. 

The per-template decision path is here. 

The full-build sequence is here. 

So the foundation is already in place. The missing layer is a formal:

resolved formatting model
2. Proposed formatting hierarchy
The new model should resolve formatting in this order:

Level 1 — Global Defaults
Level 2 — Sheet-Type Defaults
Level 3 — Data-Type Defaults
Level 4 — Column Overrides
Level 5 — Template/Special Layout Rules
The key rule:

Resolved format = inherited defaults + explicit overrides
Blank override fields should mean:

inherit
Blank should not mean invalid unless the field is required for identification, such as Header or Sheet Type.

