10. Blank-value inheritance rules
This is the most important production rule.

General rule
Blank means inherit.
Specific rules
Blank Width
  -> inherit sheet default width
  -> else inherit global default width

Blank Header Font Size
  -> inherit sheet default header font size
  -> else inherit global default header font size

Blank Data Wrap
  -> inherit sheet default wrap
  -> else inherit global default wrap

Blank Horizontal Alignment
  -> inherit sheet default horizontal alignment
  -> else inherit global default horizontal alignment

Blank Vertical Alignment
  -> inherit sheet default vertical alignment
  -> else inherit global default vertical alignment

Blank Number Format
  -> inherit from data type default
  -> else inherit global default text/number/date format

Blank Hide Column
  -> inherit sheet default hidden
  -> else false

Blank Date Column
  -> false for now
  -> later replaced by Data Type
Invalid values
Invalid values should be Dashboard Quality warnings or failures depending on severity:

Invalid width -> WARNING or FAIL
Invalid alignment -> WARNING
Invalid wrap strategy -> WARNING
Invalid number format -> WARNING/FAIL depending on impact
Invalid data type -> FAIL
Missing header -> FAIL
Duplicate header -> WARNING/FAIL depending current rule
11. Template creation behavior under resolved formatting
Current full build
The current full-build path is:

clear template if needed
resize sheet
apply template base formatting
write metadata/signature
apply freeze/tab color
final date/number format enforcement
hide template
This is centralized in buildTemplateFromDashboard_. 

Proposed new behavior
buildTemplateFromDashboard_
  -> resolveTemplateFormatPlan_
  -> clearTemplateForFullBuild_
  -> resizeSheet_
  -> applyTemplateBaseFormattingFromPlan_
       1. apply broad global/sheet defaults to title/header/data ranges
       2. apply header labels
       3. apply column widths in runs
       4. apply data-type number formats in grouped runs
       5. apply sparse column overrides
       6. apply hidden columns
       7. apply filters/alternating colors/subheaders
  -> writeTemplateMetadata_
  -> storeTemplateFormatSignature_
  -> optionally skip duplicate date/number enforcement
  -> applyTemplateFreezeAndTabColor_
  -> hideTemplateIfNeeded_
Expected benefits
fewer column-by-column format calls
clearer signature generation
faster Section G
cleaner Dashboard Quality Section D/G explanations
safer modularization later
12. Section D validation under resolved formatting
Section D should stop treating blank override cells as automatically suspicious.

Current purpose
Section D currently checks column definitions for missing, blank, duplicate, or invalid rows.

Proposed Section D quality checks
Required checks:
- Header exists
- Header is unique
- Header maps to at least one governed sheet, if that is expected
- Data Type valid, when introduced
- Width override blank or valid number
- Header Font Size override blank or valid number
- Hide override blank or valid boolean
- Wrap override blank or valid enum
- Horizontal alignment blank or valid enum
- Vertical alignment blank or valid enum
- Number format blank or valid format string

New notes:
- Blank formatting fields inherit defaults.
- Only non-default overrides are expected to be populated.
Recommended Section D output style
Column Definitions - PASS
No missing, duplicate, or invalid column definitions found.
Blank formatting fields are treated as inherited global/sheet defaults.
13. Section G validation under resolved formatting
Current Section G
Current Section G:

builds date checks from dateColumn
reads number formats from sample rows across all columns
optionally repairs failed formats
writes Framework Test 6 / Section G rows
Date checks are built from dateColumn. 

The current format read pulls sample rows across the full template width. 

Proposed Section G
runDashboardQualitySectionGDateFormatIntegrity_
  -> resolveTemplateFormatPlan_ for each template
  -> dateColumns = plan.columns where dataType is DATE or MONTH_YEAR
  -> for each date column:
       expected = resolvedColumn.numberFormat
       actual = read number formats only for that column/sample rows
       compare normalized formats
  -> write Section G rows
Recommended statuses
If audit-only:

PASS
FAIL
WARNING
If repair is retained:

PASS
PASS AFTER REPAIR
FAIL
WARNING
Recommended Section G row fields
Template
Sheet Type
Header
Column
Data Type
Expected Format
Actual Format
Status
Quality Notes
Recommended summary behavior
If all pass:

All templates | All governed sheet types | Date format columns | Governed formats | Matched | PASS | All date format checks passed.
If repairs occurred:

Template - Master List | Master List | Date of Birth | DATE | mm/dd/yyyy | repaired | PASS AFTER REPAIR | Format corrected during Section G.
14. Template signature impact
The current template flow calculates an expected signature and compares it to stored signatures before choosing metadata-only refresh or full build. 

The resolved formatting model should become part of the signature.

Recommended signature payload
{
  templateVersion,
  sheetType,
  templateName,
  rowCount,
  colCount,
  headers,
  behavior,
  globalFormatDefaultsHash,
  sheetFormatDefaultsHash,
  resolvedColumnFormatsHash,
  hiddenColumnsHash,
  dateFormatsHash,
  widthRunsHash
}
Why this matters
If a global default changes:

affected templates should rebuild
If a dashboard override changes:

only templates using that column/sheet type should rebuild
If metadata changes but resolved formatting does not:

metadata-only refresh should still be allowed
